# .clauderules

## Project Standards

### Prompt Standards
- Always include workspace context in prompts
- Reference memory bank for historical context  
- Use structured output formats (JSON, YAML)
- Include error handling in all code generation

### Code Standards
- TypeScript for all new code
- Follow ESLint configuration
- Write tests for new features
- Document API endpoints with OpenAPI

### Security Rules
- Never expose API keys in code
- Validate all user inputs
- Use parameterized queries
- Implement rate limiting

### Container Rules
- Always use least-privilege principles
- Mount only necessary volumes
- Set resource limits
- Use AppArmor profiles

### Development Workflow
1. Branch from main
2. Test in local containers
3. Run security scan
4. Submit PR with tests
5. Deploy to staging first